      "╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗",
      "║               The Art of Chinese Idioms                  ║",
      "╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝",
      "",
      "成语 (chéngyǔ) are four-character idioms that encapsulate",
      "profound wisdom, historical stories, and cultural values.",
      "",
      "Key Characteristics:",
      "• Usually 4 characters",
      "• Often have historical or literary origins",
      "• Convey complex ideas concisely",
      "• Add sophistication to language",
      "",
      "Learning Approach:",
      "1. Understand the literal meaning",
      "2. Learn the story or origin",
      "3. Grasp the metaphorical usage",
      "4. Practice using in context",
      "",
      "Example: 龙飞凤舞 (lóng fēi fèng wǔ)",
      "Literal: Dragons flying, phoenixes dancing",
      "Meaning: Vigorous, lively calligraphy or writing style",
      "",
      "Master idioms to speak like a native!"
    ]
